$ Excel: File -> Options -> Formulas

Change options related to → Microsoft/Office/Excel/formulas calculation, performance, and error handling.

{ Calculation options #xls-calculation-options

  Workbook calculation
    • Automatic
    • Automatic except for data tables
    • Manual (with tick to *Recalculate workbook before saving*)

  Enable iterative calculation

  See also → Microsoft/Office/Excel/formulas#excel-formula-recalculation[Excel formula recalculation].

}
{ Working with formulas

  Toggable options include
    • R1C1 reference style
    • Formula AutoComplete
    • Use table names in formulas
    • Use `GetPivotData` functions for PivotTable references
    • Suggest formula variations that are supported by older versions of Excel

}
{ Error Checking

  Toggable options include
    • Enable background error checking

  Choose color that indicate errors

  Button to *Reset Ignored Errors*

}
{ Error checking rules #xls-file-opt-formula-error-checking-rules

  Toggable options include
    • Cells containing formulas that result in an error
    • Inconsistent calculated column formula in tables
    • Cells containing years represented as 2 digits
    • Numbers formatted as text or preceded by an apostrophe
    • Formulas incosistent with other formulas in the region
    • Formulas which omit cells in a region
    • Unlocked cells containing formulas
    • Formulas referring to empty cells
    • Data entered in a table is invalid
    • Misleading number formats

  Compare these options with the `xlErrorChecks` enumeration which is used in the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Errors#xls-errors-item[`item()`] method of the
  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Errors[`errors` object].

}
